{
  "type": "FeatureCollection",
  "name": "Prairie ecoregions (V1.36 starter set; Saskatchewan added V2.14)",
  "comment": "Hand-drawn approximations of the prairie provinces' major terrestrial ecoregions, used by src/ecoregion.py:lookup_ecoregion. The polygons are rectangular bounding regions chosen for non-overlap rather than fidelity to natural boundaries (e.g. river valleys). Alberta features lie west of the -110 meridian (the AB/SK border, 4th meridian); Saskatchewan features lie east of it, up to the SK/MB border (~-101.4). Ecoregion keys are shared across provinces where the ecoregion is the same (aspen_parkland, mixedgrass_prairie, boreal_mixedwood) — nature does not respect borders (Design principle P1/P2); moist_mixedgrass is the SK Regina/Saskatoon belt. scripts/prepare_ecoregions.py is the documented upgrade path: replace this file with simplified polygons derived from the CEC Level III Ecoregions of North America shapefile when fidelity matters. Riparian and Wet Meadow are intentionally absent — those are per-feature rather than per-region at the provincial scale, so they remain manual-only in the plant filter.",
